2020 Boston Eviction Data

Polygon Map:

This one is probably my favorite for showing eviction filing data. It lets the user/viewer see the number of evictions in each location and put some other relevant data in.

Centroid Point Map

This is probably the least effective of the three forms, the points are small by default. To check for improvement, I tried adjusting the size by the number of filings, which is much more effective. It is nice to look at but I dont think it necessarily is betterit is harder to see what the geography is that groups the evictions.

Heat Map: Interpolated Centroids

Perhaps if I had point data for evictions filings the heat map would be more useful but as it is the size of the hot spots actually minimizes the impactit seems there are only few spots where this is happening but even then they look too isolated from each other.
